description:
I usually like cookie dough but I guess in big doses like this, it's just too overwhelmingly sweet. If you can eat a whole tub of cookie dough in one sitting, this is probably more for you. 

// T A S T E //
The place itself has about 4-5 varieties of edible cookie dough but honestly, they all taste the same to me. I ended up getting the cookie monster and s'mores dough. I did like the cookie monster one but I wasn't blown away. I got pretty sick of eating this dessert after a few bites since it made my teeth ache. I wish they also served ice cream because it would balance out the cookie dough instead of just eating straight up scoops of room temperature dough. 

// P R I C E //
This place is expensive. Two scoops of cookie dough on a cone ended up being around $13 and that was with the free toppings from checking in on Yelp! With that price range, I'd rather eat something else.

// S E R V I C E //
50/50. One of the girls working wasn't the friendliest and seemed really annoyed when people wanted to try samples. However, the cashier was pretty nice and cheery! 

Cool concept and should be tried once! It's just not for me and people who don't prefer overly sweet desserts.

Bonus points for the cool wall with a neon sign for Instagram posts!
